<TITLE> CID speaks to Hasina about grenade attack Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  A senior prisons official Wednesday said investigators would talk with former prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Thursday about the August 21 grenade attack. Deputy inspector general (prisons) major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com that the Criminal Investigation Department (CID) was slated to meet Hasina at noon. CID additional superintendent of police Abdullah Aref told bdnews24.com that he would be accompanied by CID officials on a visit to the special jail to talk to the Awami League president. The CID sent a letter to jail authorities on November 18 asking them to schedule a meeting with Hasina. It also sent a letter to Hasina in this regard. On Nov 13, the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court granted a CID appeal to have talks with Hasina in jail. bdnew
